The paper deals with the problem of efficient placement of sensors to ensure coverage of a given area while minimizing energy consumption. This problem is related to several sub-fields of computer science, including multi-agent systems (cs.MA), information theory (cs.IT), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The focus on sensor placement and coverage suggests that cs.MA and cs.IT are the most likely categories, followed by cs.DS and cs.GT, while cs.SI is less likely but still a possibility.
